{"ID":270254, "Text":"<div class=\"page\"><div class=\"pageNum\"><a name=\"254\"><\/a><div class=\"prev\"><a href=\"stpjs253.html\">Prev<\/a><\/div><div class=\"next\"><a href=\"stpjs255.html\">Next<\/a><\/div>\n\t\t\t    STPJS 254<\/div>\n  <p class=\"cont\">build the Temple<span class=\"footRef\">1<\/span> and the Nauvoo House;<span class=\"footRef\">2<\/span> and that command is as binding upon us as any other;\n  and that man who engages not in these things is as much a transgressor as though he broke any other\n  commandment; he is not a doer of God&rsquo;s will,<span class=\"footRef\">3<\/span> not a fulfiller of His laws.<span class=\"footRef\">4<\/span><\/p>\n  <div class=\"topic \">The Saints Subject to Divine Counsel<\/div>\n  <p class=\"std\">In regard to the building up of Zion,<span class=\"footRef\">5<\/span> it has to be done by the counsel of Jehovah, by the\n  revelations of heaven; and we should feel to say, &ldquo;If the Lord go not with us, carry us not up\n  hence.&rdquo;<span class=\"footRef\">6<\/span> We would say to the Saints that come here, we have laid the foundation for the gathering\n  of God&rsquo;s people<span class=\"footRef\">7<\/span> to this place, and they expect that when the Saints do come, they will be under the\n  counsel that God has appointed.<span class=\"footRef\">8<\/span> The Twelve are set apart to counsel the Saints pertaining to this\n  matter; and we expect that those who come here will send before them their wise men<span class=\"footRef\">9<\/span> according\n  to revelation; or if not practicable, be subject to the counsel that God has given,<span class=\"footRef\">10<\/span> or they cannot\n  receive an inheritance<span class=\"footRef\">11<\/span> among the Saints, or be considered as God&rsquo;s people,<span class=\"footRef\">12<\/span> and they will be dealt\n  with as transgressors<span class=\"footRef\">13<\/span> of the laws of God.<span class=\"footRef\">14<\/span> We are trying here to gird up our loins,<span class=\"footRef\">15<\/span> and purge from\n  our midst the workers of iniquity;<span class=\"footRef\">16<\/span> and we hope that when our brethren arrive from abroad, they will\n  assist us to roll forth this good work,<span class=\"footRef\">17<\/span> and to accomplish this great design that &ldquo;Zion may be built\n  up in righteousness;<span class=\"footRef\">18<\/span> and all nations flock to her standard;&rdquo;<span class=\"footRef\">19<\/span> that as God&rsquo;s people, under His\n  direction, and obedient to His law,<span class=\"footRef\">20<\/span> we may grow up in righteousness and truth;<span class=\"footRef\">21<\/span> that when His\n  purposes shall be accomplished,<span class=\"footRef\">22<\/span> we may receive an inheritance among those that are sanctified.<span class=\"footRef\">23<\/span>\n  (July 15, 1842.) DHC 5:61-66.<\/p>\n  <div class=\"topic \">Letter of the Prophet to Governor Carlin &mdash;<\/div>\n  <div class=\"topic \">Satisfied with the Governor&rsquo;s Attitude<\/div>\n  <p class=\"std\">Esteemed Sir:&mdash;Your favor of the 27th instant per Brevet Major-General Wilson Law is before\n  me. I cannot let this opportunity pass without tendering to you my warmest thanks for the friendly\n  treatment my lady as well as those with her received at your hands during the late visit, and also for\n  the friendly feelings breathed forth in your letter. Your Excellency<\/p>\n  <div class=\"footnotes\">\n    <div class=\"footnote\">1. \n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"115976\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 115976)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(115976)\">D&amp;C 124:39<\/a><\/span>\n    <\/div>\n    <div class=\"footnote\">2. \n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"116007\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 116007)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(116007)\">D&amp;C 124:60<\/a><\/span>\n    <\/div>\n    <div class=\"footnote\">3. \n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"110351\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 110351)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(110351)\">James 1:22,25<\/a><\/span>\n    <\/div>\n    <div class=\"footnote\">4. \n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"109250\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 109250)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(109250)\">Rom. 2:13<\/a><\/span>\n    <\/div>\n    <div class=\"footnote\">5. \n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"115286\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 115286)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(115286)\">D&amp;C 103:11<\/a><\/span>\n    <\/div>\n    <div class=\"footnote\">6. \n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"106215\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 106215)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(106215)\">Ex. 35:15<\/a><\/span>\n    <\/div>\n    <div class=\"footnote\">7. \n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"114239\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 114239)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(114239)\">D&amp;C 64:33,38,41-42<\/a><\/span>\n    <\/div>\n    <div class=\"footnote\">8. \n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"115150\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 115150)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(115150)\">D&amp;C 100:2<\/a><\/span>\n    <\/div>\n    <div class=\"footnote\">9. \n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"115221\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 115221)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(115221)\">D&amp;C 101:67-68,73-74<\/a><\/span>;\n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"115295\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 115295)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(115295)\">D&amp;C 103:23<\/a><\/span>;\n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"115372\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 115372)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:v